          "id": "b99f22eb9787063a84c0624cca3945b82dc1d04d",
          "message": "fix(ci): preserve dev/ by explicit copy instead of unreliable clean-exclude\n\nclean-exclude: dev did not reliably preserve dev/bench/data.js across\nJamesIves force-pushes, causing benchmark history to be wiped on each\ngh-pages deploy. Explicitly fetch and copy the entire dev/ directory from\nthe gh-pages branch into docs/ before deploying, so the benchmark data is\nalways included in the deployed source.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
